@jessiedotjs I've been fasting off and on for years so if you need help, lmk! Also fasting isn't for everyone! If you find after a few weeks you don't feel good, it's okay to stop. Doesn't make u a failure it means your body can't do this one thing and that's okay!

@jessiedotjs It's also best to start incrementally. If you find a 24 hr fast is too challenging, start with 8-10hrs and build yourself up! I do mine for mental benefits as it helps with my adhd. But only when I have to focus on one job. (school and work and hw at the same time was too much)

@jessiedotjs Usually it's best to just stick with black coffee, unsweet tea, and water (sparkling water is my fave), but the most important thing is to make it easy and sustainable and to listen to your body! So if that means diet soda in the beginning, it's okay!

@jessiedotjs I do IF but I usually do it to how I'm feeling. If you're hungry it's bc your body isn't used to it and is also probably thirsty! Sometimes I'll skip dinner and then skip breakfast and it's as easy as that (for me)
